  "why_it_matters_templates": {
    "data_release+agriculture": "Machinery registration data drives Kramp's medium-term spare-parts demand model. Direction of new registrations sets the trajectory for the installed base 2-4 years out; downturns increase aftermarket share of dealer revenue and lift wear-part demand as farmers extend fleet life.",
    "association_report+agriculture": "Association barometers (CEMA/national) are the most reliable leading indicator of dealer purchasing intent 2 quarters ahead. Kramp order intake historically tracks these with a ~1-quarter lag.",
    "oem_financial_result+agriculture": "OEM quarterly results reveal channel inventory, dealer health and outlook \u2014 the same dealers Kramp sells to. Guidance downgrades typically signal aftermarket share gains for Kramp within 6 months.",
    "weather_crop_update+agriculture": "Weather and crop conditions drive farmer cash-flow and short-term maintenance decisions. Drought/flood events lift wear-part demand (breakdowns) but suppress new-machine investment.",
    "regulation_policy+agriculture": "Regulatory changes reshape farmer economics and equipment purchase timing. Stage V, CAP, and emissions rules affect which machines dealers order, and therefore which parts Kramp must stock.",
    "macroeconomic_update+macro": "Interest-rate and input-cost changes directly hit farmer investment capacity. Lower rates + stable fuel = new-machine purchases; higher rates + volatile fuel = deferred capex and higher parts/repair spend (Kramp positive).",
    "data_release+construction": "Construction equipment demand tracks building permits and PMI with a 1-2 quarter lag. Kramp's construction/small earth-moving assortment is exposed to compact-equipment dealer inventory.",
    "association_report+construction": "CECE reports set the benchmark for construction equipment sales expectations and directly inform Kramp's construction-segment stocking decisions.",
    "competitor_news+competitors": "Competitor moves in Kramp's channel (new dealer wins, geographic expansion, category launches) require pricing and assortment response, especially in Benelux/DACH/UK home markets.",
    "supplier_news+suppliers": "Supplier availability, pricing and category-range decisions flow directly into Kramp's stocked SKU strategy and margin.",
    "data_release+forest_landscaping": "EGMF and outdoor-power-equipment data determine the F&L segment growth assumption. Battery/robotic mower penetration reshapes the wear-part mix (blades, batteries) Kramp must carry.",
    "regulation_policy+construction": "Emissions and safety regulation (Stage V, CE) forces fleet renewal cycles which cascade into spare-part specs and dealer stocking. Kramp assortment must track homologation windows.",
    "regulation_policy+macro": "EU-level policy (CBAM, right-to-repair, spare-parts directive) affects Kramp's cross-border business economics and independent-channel positioning vs OEM captive parts.",
    "default": "Signal is relevant to Kramp's commercial planning; review for aftermarket, pricing, assortment or country-strategy implications."
  },
